    <note>Wang(2) Han [1810] Qi(2)'s [1765] and Gui(1)'s [1845] uncle (Gui(1) was the son of Han's elder brother). Di(1) Fei's [1633] son-in-law. His wife, surname Di (1001-1069), was buried in Zhenjiang, Dantu county. Father-in-law of Chao(2) Zongque's [8001] and Chao(2) Zongke's [7121] son and/or nephew, Zhongwei [3014], and of Tang(2) Jie's [1593] son, Shuwen [3830], Zheng(1) You's [429] grandfather-in-law. XCB, 173.1b-2a has details on the port of Canton. XCB, 173.1b-2b, 4b, 185.12a, 187.15a; Guangxi TZ, 16.13a; Guangdong TZ, 14.25b, 26a; SHY:ZG, 65.9a-9b; Wang Gui, WJ, 57.7b-9b (wife, surname Di, who married him at age 17 and died in 1069 at age 69). CBD, 1, 120.</note>
